China's First Qualifying Exam for Auctioneers 
China held its first qualifying exam for auctioneers in Shanghai today,
with 131 auctioneers from around the country sitting for it.
China's first batch of licensed auctioneers will be come from these
examinees.
The examination was held by the Ministry of Internal Trade and the
Ministry of Personnel.
According to China's Auction Law, which went into effect on January 1,
auctions must be held by auctioneers, and the Ministry of Internal
Trade and the Ministry of Personnel have jointly issued provisional
regulations on the necessary qualifications of these auctioneers, and
an auctioneers qualifying exam committee has been set up.
Auction houses that operate without licensed auctioneers will not be
allowed to handle any auctions in the future.
